<br>
I applied an Anime-like style to my APart portfolio. I kept it very suddle and kept is far away from being trite as I could. I also didn't make any fan pieces for an &quot;art&quot; class. I ending up getting a &quot;3&quot; and passing. <br>
<br>
A friend of mine did a similar thing but his work was more like character design illustration. His work was excellent and I knew the teacher liked his portfolio. She wasn't all that confident about it though. Unfortunantly he did not pass. <br>
<br>
I'll agree that people are arrogant to new concepts like Anime. I feel  as though I'm being driven underground because of my hobby. But I will go on knowing that arrogant people are only blissfully held up by their facade of &quot;real life&quot;. I look at these disgusting &quot;normal&quot; people seeing how ignorant and boring they are.<br>
<br>
As for Oprah, I didn't know she said such things. I'd be obliged to put into a coma just because of the kind of person she is. I bet she'd be alot of fun to beat up. <br>
<br>
Go watch &quot;Otaku no Video&quot;. I know it obscures Otaku but, I find it inspiring.<br>
<br>
Wobb<br>
